===Pronunciation===
*{{a|UK}} {{IPA|/ɹiːˈlɪv/|lang=en}}

===Verb===
{{en-verb|relives|reliving|relived|relived}}

# {{context|obsolete|transitive|lang=en}} To bring back to life; to [[revive]], [[resuscitate]]. {{defdate|16th-17th c.}}
#*'''1590''', {{w|Edmund Spenser}}, ''The Faerie Queene'', III.4:
#*:Had she not beene devoide of mortall slime, / Shee should not then have bene '''relyv'd''' againe [...].
# {{context|intransitive|lang=en}} To come back to life.
# {{context|transitive|lang=en}} To [[experience]] (something) again; to live over again. {{defdate|from 18th c.}}
#:''I relive that horrible accident every night and wake screaming, just as I screamed when it happened.''

